<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="U" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Unkindness" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Unkindness,</orth> 1) want of love and tenderness: <bibl n="shak. ven 478" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 478</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 120.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 120, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.139.2" default="NO" valid="yes">139, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.250" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 250</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.563" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 563</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.133" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.96" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.4.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 4, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.137" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 4, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.159" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.159" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 159</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 138</bibl> <emph>(an u.).</emph>
<lb />2) ill-will, grudge, a disposition to fall out and quarrel: <cit><quote>we shall drink down all u.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.204" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 204</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>take no u. of his hasty words,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 169</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>is there any u. between my lord and you?</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.5.35" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 5, 35</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in this I bury all u.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 159</bibl></cit>.
